Journal.Title: Journal of Asian natural products research

Article.ArticleTitle: Two new sesquiterpenoid glycosides from the leaves of Lycium barbarum.

AbstractText: Two new sesquiterpenoid glycosides, lyciumionosides A-B (1-2), together with four known compounds (3-6), were isolated from the leaves of Lycium barbarum. Their structures were mainly established on the basis of MS, 1D and 2D NMR spectroscopic techniques. The antiproliferative activities of compounds 1-5 were evaluated. Compound 1 showed highest inhibitory activity against A549 cells with IC50 value of 32.6 ± 2.6 μM, compound 3 showed highest inhibitory activity against PC-3 cells with IC50 value of 36.0 ± 2.9 μM, and compound 5 exhibited highest inhibitory activity against HeLa cells with IC50 value of 32.3 ± 4.2 μM.
